{"id":"1","user_id":"1","privacy_id":null,"title":"Welcome","slug":"Welcome","position":null,"type":null,"lang":null,"caption":"Bootie is easy.","comments":null,"content":"<p>PHP 5 Micro Web Application Framework based on Micromvc by David Pennington.<\/p><p>Improvements<\/p><p><br><\/p><ul><li>Dispatching method simplification<\/li><li>Routing request method based<\/li><li>Filters<\/li><li>Model pagination<\/li><li>Flash messages<br><\/li><\/ul>","created":"1443889302","updated":"1443889446"}
{"id":"2","user_id":"1","privacy_id":null,"title":"Models","slug":"Models","position":null,"type":null,"lang":null,"caption":"Models tell ORM how to relate database objects.","comments":null,"content":"<p>You can relate models just like in Laravel.<\/p><p>If you want to relate two models you can use the following for a 1 -&gt; n relation<br><\/p><pre>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public static $has = [<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'files' =&gt; '\\Model\\File'<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ];<br><\/pre><p><br><\/p><p>If you want to relate two models using a pivot table you can add this directive<\/p><pre>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public static $has_many_through = [<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'tags' =&gt; [<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'post_id' =&gt; '\\Model\\PostTag',<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'tag_id' =&gt; '\\Model\\Tag',<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ]<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ];<br><\/pre>","created":"1443889449","updated":"1443889749"}
{"id":"3","user_id":"1","privacy_id":null,"title":"Controllers","slug":"Controllers","position":null,"type":null,"lang":null,"caption":"Controllers perform actions on the server side","comments":null,"content":"<p>You can select, write or update to Database using controllers.<\/p><p>If you want to retrieve a paginated list, you can use <\/p><pre>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public function index(){<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entries = \\Model\\Post::paginate([<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'updated' =&gt; \"DESC\"<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ]);<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return \\Bootie\\App::view('admin.posts.index',[<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'entries'&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&gt; $entries<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ]);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<\/pre><p><br><\/p><p>If you want to update a record<\/p><pre>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public function update($path,$id){<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; if(is_numeric($id))<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; extract($_POST);<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entry = new \\Model\\Post();<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entry-&gt;id = $id;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entry-&gt;title = $title;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entry-&gt;slug = sanitize($title,false);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entry-&gt;caption = $caption;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entry-&gt;content = $content;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $entry-&gt;updated = TIME;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; $result = $entry-&gt;save();<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return redirect('\/admin\/posts',[<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'success' =&gt; \"Entry &lt;strong&gt;{$entry-&gt;title}&lt;\/strong&gt; has been updated\"<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ]);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return redirect('\/admin\/posts',[<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'danger' =&gt; \"Entry ID was not provided\"<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ]);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br><\/pre>","created":"1443889753","updated":"1443889950"}
{"id":"4","user_id":"1","privacy_id":null,"title":"Routes","slug":"Routes","position":null,"type":null,"lang":null,"caption":"Routes establishes valid pathways to actions and views","comments":null,"content":"<p>In order to perform actions you must establish a pathway to controllers.<\/p><p>If you want to show a static page you can set a route like this<\/p><pre>App::route('\/([^\/]+)', [ 'uses' =&gt; 'Controller\\HomeController@page']);<\/pre><p><br><\/p><p>Then, perform the action in the controller<\/p><pre>&lt;?php namespace Controller;<br><br>class HomeController extends \\Controller\\BaseController {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; static $layout = \"default\";<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public function page($page){<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return \\Bootie\\App::view($page);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br>}<br><\/pre><p><br><\/p>","created":"1443889956","updated":"1443890132"}
{"id":"5","user_id":"1","privacy_id":null,"title":"Filters","slug":"Filters","position":null,"type":null,"lang":null,"caption":"You can add filters to ensure proper access to actions and views","comments":null,"content":"<p>If you want, for example to allow access to actions only to admin users you must set a reference in the route with the key before<\/p><pre>App::route('\/admin', &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; [ 'uses' =&gt; 'Controller\\AdminController@index','before' =&gt; 'auth.admin']);<\/pre><p><br><\/p><p>Then, declare the filter<\/p><pre>App::filter('auth.admin',function(){<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; if( ! session('user_id') || session('group') !== 'admin'){<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return redirect('\/login','Your session has expired');<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br>});<br><\/pre><p><br><\/p>","created":"1443890135","updated":"1443890273"}
{"id":"6","user_id":"1","privacy_id":null,"title":"Flash Messages","slug":"Flash-Messages","position":null,"type":null,"lang":null,"caption":"You can pass messages from an action to a view with flash messages","comments":null,"content":"<p>You can message the user about the results of the action using the redirect function.<\/p><p>In the controller call this<\/p><pre>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return redirect('\/admin\/posts',[<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'success' =&gt; \"Entry &lt;strong&gt;{$entry-&gt;title}&lt;\/strong&gt; has been updated\"<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ]);<\/pre><p><br><\/p><p>Then, in the view invoke the messages<\/p><pre>&lt;?php echo messages();?&gt;<br><\/pre>","created":"1443890281","updated":"1443890460"}
{"id":"7","user_id":"1","privacy_id":null,"title":"Views","slug":"Views","position":null,"type":null,"lang":null,"caption":"You can include any view when you are finished with your controller action.","comments":null,"content":"<p>The way to return a view is the following<\/p><pre>return \\Bootie\\App::view('admin.posts.edit',[<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 'entry'&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&gt; $entry<br>]);<\/pre><p>Dataset will be passed in the second argument.<br><\/p><p><br><\/p>","created":"1443890475","updated":"1443890600"}
